          "body": "Verse 28 is one of the New Testament's clearest statements of ministry-priority: *first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, then miracles, then gifts of healings, helps, administrations, various kinds of tongues*. The ranking is intentional. The word-ministries (apostles, prophets, teachers) come first; the sign-ministries (miracles, healings, tongues) follow. Tongues—the Corinthian favorite—comes *last*. Paul is not deprecating tongues (he claims more of it than any of them, 14:18), but he is dismantling the Corinthian hierarchy by replacing it with the divine one. The rhetorical questions of vv. 29-30 (*all are not apostles, are they?*) use a Greek construction that expects *no* as the answer. The expected answer in every case is *no*. No believer has every gift; no gift is given to every believer; the church needs every member precisely because no member is sufficient."
